description:
You are given an array of integers. Move all positive numbers to the right side and all negative numbers to the left side of the array. Maintain the relative order of positive and negative numbers within their respective sections.

#### `Input Format:`
- `First line contains length of the array `
- `Second line consists space separated an array of integers.`

#### `Output Format:`
- `Print the modified array where positive numbers are on the right side and negative numbers are on the left side.`

#### `Sample Input:`
```
8
3 -1 4 -2 0 -5 8 -7
```

#### `Sample Output:`
```
-1 -2 -5 -7 3 4 0 8 
```

#### `Constraints:`
- `The array can have both positive and negative integers.`
- `The array may contain duplicate elements.`
- `The size of the array is between 1 and 10^4.`
title: Rearrange Positive and Negative Numbers
